@startuml class_calculator

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class Calculator {
    - _history : list[dict]
    + __init__() : None
    + get_history() : list[dict]
    + clear_history() : None
    + add(a, b) : numeric
    + subtract(a, b) : numeric
    + multiply(a, b) : numeric
    + divide(a, b) : numeric
    + square(a) : numeric
    + cube(a) : numeric
    + square_root(a) : numeric
    + cube_root(a) : numeric
    + factorial(n) : int
    + power(base, exp) : numeric
    + log(a) : numeric
    + ln(a) : numeric
    - _record_operation(operation_name: str, operands: list, result: numeric) : None
}

note right of Calculator::_history
  Stores list of dicts:
  {operation, operands, result}
end note

note right of Calculator::_record_operation
  Called internally by every
  operation method on success.
  Never called when an exception
  is raised.
end note

class MaxRetriesExceeded <<Exception>> {
}

package "cli.py" <<module>> {
    class CLIFunctions <<utility>> {
        + run_calculator() : None
        + display_history(calc: Calculator) : None
        + prompt_for_first_number() : numeric
        + prompt_for_operator() : str
        + prompt_for_second_number() : numeric
        + display_result(result: numeric) : None
        + display_error(error: Exception) : None
        - _format_history_entry(index: int, entry: dict) : str
    }
}

CLIFunctions --> Calculator : uses
CLIFunctions ..> MaxRetriesExceeded : raises

note on link
  display_history() calls
  get_history() then
  _format_history_entry()
  for each entry
end note

@enduml
